list.item:
Sweden is by far the strongest Western military force in Northern Europe.
                        Although not a member of NATO, Sweden is an important factor in NATO
                        planning and defense;

Sweden’s continued ability to deny its territory and air space to the USSR
                        will greatly simplify the defense of Northern Norway, and allow additional
                        time for allied reinforcement of that area;

Approval would be consistent with our long-standing policy of supporting
                        Swedish defense forces through the provision of sophisticated U.S. military
                        systems and technology;
